C aur C++ dono hi programming languages hain, lekin inmein kuch mahatvapurn farq hain:

Programming Paradigm:
C: Procedural programming language hai. Ismein functions ke zariye programming ki jaati hai.
C++: Object-oriented programming (OOP) language hai. Ismein classes aur objects ka istemal hota hai, jo data aur functions ko encapsulate karte hain.
Data Abstraction:
C: Data ko functions se alag rakha jata hai.
C++: Encapsulation ke zariye data aur methods ko ek saath rakhne ki suvidha milti hai.
Inheritance:
C: Ismein inheritance ka concept nahi hai.
C++: Inheritance ki suvidha milti hai, jisse ek class doosri class se properties aur methods inherit kar sakti hai.
Polymorphism:
C: Polymorphism ka concept nahi hai.
C++: Function overloading aur operator overloading ke zariye polymorphism ki suvidha di jaati hai.
Standard Template Library (STL):
C: STL nahi hoti.
C++: STL ka istemal karke algorithms aur data structures ka istemal aasani se kiya ja sakta hai.
Memory Management:
C: Memory allocation aur deallocation manual hoti hai (malloc, free).
C++: Memory management mein constructors aur destructors ka istemal hota hai, jo automatic clean-up karte hain.
Syntax:
C: Simple aur straightforward syntax hai.
C++: Thoda complex syntax hai, kyunki ismein OOP features hote hain.
In dono languages ka istemal alag-alag situations mein hota hai. C aksar system programming aur embedded systems ke liye istemal hota hai, jabki C++ game development, application software, aur large systems ke liye popular hai.



